      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">This Infantry or Gun Unit may add a 3-ton Lorry Transport Attachment. The number of vehicles in the Unit is as follows:Add one 3-ton Lorry Transport for every five Infantry Teams in the Unit.Add one 3-ton Lorry Transport for each Gun Team in the Unit.The characteristics of a 3-ton Lorry Transport are shown below.
MOTIVATIONCONFIDENT4+
SKILLTRAINED4+
IS HIT ONCAREFULL4+
SAVETANK5+
TACTICALTERRAIN DASHCROSS COUNTRY DASHROAD DASHCROSS-10&quot;/25cm12&quot;/30cm28&quot;/70cm4+SPECIAL RULESPassengers 5, Tractor: Team can carry five Infantry Teams or one Gun Team as Passengers.Softskin: If a Transport is Destroyed, any Passengers it is carrying are also Destroyed, and all Transports must be Sent to the Rear immediately. All Passengers must Dismount from this Unit at the same time. Empty Transport Teams must be Sent to the Rear.  
Unarmoured: Team cannot Charge into Contact and must Break Off if Assaulted.</characteristic>
        <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">British, Build, Unit (any Rifle Company HQ, any Rifle Platoon, 25 pdr Field Battery, 17 pdr Ant-Tank Platoon)</characteristic>
