  <sharedSelectionEntries>




















  </sharedSelectionEntries>
  <sharedRules>
    <rule id="612e-97f4-b2a0-4a1f" name="Bunker Killer" hidden="false">
      <description>Bunker Killer teams can hit Nest and Bunder Teams despite being an Artillery Bombardment. As a Brutal weapon, any Infantry, Gun (including Nests and Bunkers), or Unarmoured Tank Teams it hits must re-roll successful Saves.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="dc95-6fc9-07d2-e005" name="Petard" hidden="false">
      <description>When firing a Bombardment with their Petard, AVRE teams:
May spot and fire Bombardments even if they moved this turn.
Do not need to re-roll successful rolls To Hit for only having 1 or 2 weapons firing, and
Ignore the Danger Close rule.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="83b0-ae8a-ebc7-8259" name="Flame Trailers" hidden="false">
      <description>Flame tanks cannot Charge into Contact and cannot Hold Objectives.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="37a1-579b-9530-017d" name="Flame-thrower" hidden="false">
      <description>Infantry, Gun and Unarmoured Tank Teams re-roll successful Saves when hit by a Flame-thrower and the Unit is automatically Pinned Down. Armoured Tank Teams use their Top armour for Armour Saves when hit by a Flame-thrower.

Flame-throwers my shoot in Defensive Fire. Howeverm while a Unit that is Hit by a Flame-thrower is Pinned Down, this does not automatically stop the assault, The defender still needs to score five (or eight) hits to sop the assault as normal.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="ff11-a653-d1b2-5d2f" name="Airborne" publicationId="10a4-8008-66c3-952e" hidden="false">
      <description>This Formation may make an Airborne Assault in missions that use the Airborden Assault rules (page 84)</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="d352-df91-7d69-ab94" name="Mike Target" hidden="false">
      <description>When a Spotting Team successfully Rages In an Artillery Unit with Mike Target, they may immediatly roll to Range In another Artillery Unit. If successful, the additional Artillery Unit is treated as Ranging In on the same attempt as the first.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="9b1d-a6d6-63e6-186d" name="Night Attack" hidden="false">
      <description>If a Force with Night Attack is the attacker in a mission where the defender has Minefields, the player may attack at night. If they do so, Night Fighting rules (see page 113 of the rulebook) are in effect at the start of the game.

British Units from a Formation with  Night Attack can move freely from the start of the game. Friendly Units from other Formations or Support may not more out of their Deployment Area untill morning breaks.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="f5ee-b28e-e76b-3f6e" name="Air Observer Post" hidden="false">
      <description>An Air Observer Post is an Aircraft that arrives on a roll of 3+ (rather than the usual 4+)

An Air Observer Post is unarmed, but can act as an Observer Spotting for an Artillery Bombardment with an Aiming Pont within 12&quot;/30cm of tha Aircraft. The opposing player may shoot at the Aircraft immediately before it rolls to Range In as though the aircraft was Shooting.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="093d-5393-272f-d75a" name="Unit Transport" hidden="false">
      <description>The Unit Leader of the Transport Attachment must end the Movement Step within 6&quot;/15cm of the Unit Leader of its Passenger Unit while on the table. If it cannot do this, then the Transport Attachment must be Sent to the Rear (see page 45 of the rulebook)</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="885e-625f-2abf-4155" name="Mind and Heart" hidden="false">
      <description>Teams from the Commando Troop HQ and Commando Sections in this Formation that start their Movement Step adjecent to a cliff (or similar Impassable terrain feature) roll a Skill Test. If successful, the team may cross the terrain at Terrain Dash speed.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="b47f-e6a2-8976-4e00" name="Already Here" hidden="false">
      <description>This Platoon counts as being 0 points when calculating reserves.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="45f4-60f0-dcef-de8b" name="Pioneers" hidden="false">
      <description>Infantry teams in this Formation&apos;s Rifle Platoons cross Minefields safely on a roll of 3+ and Dig In on a roll of 3+.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="6d39-c30e-208c-707c" name="Passengers 5" hidden="false">
      <description>Team can carry five Infantry Team as Passangers</description>
    </rule>
  </sharedRules>
